.SS "blendToAnimation (int animationId, number blendTime)"

.PP
Smoothly blend from current Spriter animation to a new Spriter animation by ID over the specified time\&. This function smoothly transitions from the current animation to a new animation by interpolating between the two over the specified blend time\&. The blend creates a seamless transition between animations\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIanimationId\fP The ID of the target animation to blend to 
.br
\fIblendTime\fP The duration of the blend transition in seconds
.RE
.PP
The blend operation interpolates between the current animation frame and the corresponding frame in the target animation\&. This creates a smooth transition that maintains the sprite's visual continuity\&.

.PP
During the blend, the sprite will emit animation events and can be monitored for blend completion\&. The blend time determines how quickly the transition occurs\&.

.PP
\fBWarning\fP
.RS 4
If the target animation ID is invalid, the blend will fail silently 

.PP
This only works for blending between Spriter animations
.RE
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
The blend time must be positive (greater than 0) 

.PP
If no animation is currently playing, the new animation will start immediately
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
true if the blend was successfully initiated, false otherwise
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBSprite::blendToAnimation(string, number)\fP 

.PP
\fBSprite::onAnimationBlendComplete()\fP 

.PP
\fBSprite::isBlending()\fP 

.PP
\fBSprite::getBlendProgress()\fP 
.RE
.PP

