.SS "setPostDrawHelper (\fBISpriteDrawHelper\fP helper)"

.PP
sets a helper that draws additional content after the sprite is rendered This function sets a custom drawing helper that will be called after the sprite has been rendered\&. This allows for additional custom drawing operations to be performed on top of the sprite\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIhelper\fP The \fBISpriteDrawHelper\fP object that will handle the post-draw operations
.RE
.PP
The post-draw helper is called after the sprite has been completely rendered, allowing for additional drawing operations such as overlays, effects, or custom graphics to be drawn on top of the sprite\&.

.PP
The helper object must implement the \fBISpriteDrawHelper\fP interface, which provides access to the drawing context and sprite information needed for custom drawing operations\&.

.PP
\fBWarning\fP
.RS 4
The helper will be called every frame while the sprite is visible, so performance should be considered 
.RE
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
The helper has access to the same drawing context as the sprite 

.PP
Setting a new helper will replace any previously set helper
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
\fBISpriteDrawHelper\fP 

.PP
Sprite::setPreDrawHelper() 
.RE
.PP

