.SS "useCollisionMask (\fBImage\fP frameImage, \fBImage\fP maskImage)"

.PP
sets collision masks for precise collision detection using image data This function enables pixel-perfect collision detection for the sprite by using image data to define collision areas\&. This provides more accurate collision detection than simple rectangular bounds\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIframeImage\fP The image containing the frame data to use for collision detection 
.br
\fImaskImage\fP The image containing the collision mask (white pixels = collision, black pixels = no collision)
.RE
.PP
The collision mask system uses the alpha channel or brightness of the maskImage to determine collision areas\&. White pixels (or pixels with alpha > 0) are considered solid collision areas, while black pixels (or pixels with alpha = 0) are considered empty space\&.

.PP
This allows for precise collision detection that matches the visual appearance of the sprite, rather than using simple rectangular bounds\&.

.PP
\fBWarning\fP
.RS 4
Collision mask detection is more computationally expensive than rectangular collision detection 
.RE
.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
The maskImage should be the same size as the frameImage 

.PP
Only the alpha channel or brightness of the maskImage is used for collision detection
.RE
.PP
\fBSee also\fP
.RS 4
Sprite::setCollisionBounds() 

.PP
Sprite::getCollisionBounds() 
.RE
.PP


